Source: kwin-ctm-monitor
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Charles Jones <charles.jones@valencesoftware.io>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), python3
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/cjones26/kwin-ctm-monitor

Package: kwin-ctm-monitor
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, apt-utils, docker.io | docker-ce, dpkg-dev, gnupg,
 kmod, patch, python3
Description: Preserve a configurable KWin CTM patch across KDE neon updates
 Watches APT metadata, builds a matching patched KWin in an isolated container,
 and publishes validated packages to a signed local APT repository. It does not
 install KWin; Discover or pkcon remains responsible for installation.
